  "prompt": "Where can I get a large corpus of news articles with pictures?",
  "response": "There are several sources where you can obtain large collections of news articles with images:\n\n1. News API services:\n- NewsAPI.org\n- GDELT Project\n- Webhose.io\n\n2. Academic and research datasets:\n- Common Crawl\n- Stanford Large-Scale News Dataset\n- NewsNet dataset\n\n3. Public repositories:\n- Kaggle news datasets\n- Google Dataset Search\n- Internet Archive\n\n4. Commercial sources:\n- LexisNexis\n- ProQuest\n- Factiva\n\n5. Open source collections:\n- Reuters Corpus\n- BBC News Dataset\n- Wikipedia News archives\n\nThe availability and licensing will vary, so check the specific terms for each source. Some may require subscriptions or have usage restrictions.\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any of these sources or help you understand their specific characteristics?",
